Module com.example.turinggame
Package Model

Class Problem

java.lang.Object
Model.Problem
public class Problem extends Object
The Problem class represents a specific problem or challenge involving a secret code and a set of validators. It manages the rounds of validation, the secret code, and the validators involved in the problem.

  • Method Details

    • nextRound

      public void nextRound()
      Advances to the next round in the problem. Adds a new Round to the rounds list and increments the current round counter.

    • previousRound

      public void previousRound()
      Goes back to the previous round in the problem. Removes the last round from the rounds list and decrements the current round counter.

    • addCodeAtRound

      public void addCodeAtRound(int code)
      Adds a code to the current round. Throws a TuringException if a code is added after testing a validator.
      Parameters:
      code - The code to be added to the current round.
      Throws:
      TuringException - If a code is added after a validator has been tested.
